description: Learned borrowing from Latin sinus (“a bent surface, curve, hollow”). Doublet of sine.

entries.meaning: (anatomy, zootomy) A pouch or cavity in a bone or other tissue, especially one in the bones of the face or skull connecting with the nasal cavities (the paranasal sinus).
examples: Hyponyms: ethmoid sinus, frontal sinus, maxillary sinus, paranasal sinus, piriform sinus, Rokitansky-Aschoff sinus, sphenoid sinus

definitionGroups.group: (anatomy) An irregular venous or lymphatic cavity, reservoir, or dilated vessel.

entries.meaning: (physiology, attributive) Relating to or denoting the sinoatrial node of the heart or its function of regulating the heartbeat.
(pathology) An abnormal cavity or passage such as a fistula, leading from a deep-seated infection and discharging pus to the surface.
(botany) A rounded notch or depression between two lobes or teeth in the margin of a leaf or petal.
(geography) A bay of the sea; a recess in the shore.
